<subSubSection pageId="45" pageNumber="46" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1437,151,717]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,151,176]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Remarks.</emphasis>
Some specimens differ from the re-description of the species provided by Peña Cantero 
<emphasis box="[1300,1355,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">et al.</emphasis>
(1996) and the diagnoses of the species by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pena Cantero, A. L. &amp; Vervoort, W." box="[560,934,188,213]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="795 - 818" refId="ref46024" refString="Pena Cantero, A. L. &amp; Vervoort, W. (2005) Species of Schizotricha Allman, 1883 (Cnidaria: Hydrozoa: Halopterididae) from US Antarctic expeditions with the description of two new species. Journal of Natural History, 39, 795 - 818. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930400001541" type="journal article" year="2005">Peña Cantero &amp; Vervoort (2005)</bibRefCitation>
. The materials from the stations ANT XV/ 
<date pageId="45" pageNumber="46" value="1948-03-05">3 48-5</date>
, 48-63, 48-220, ANT XXI/2 PS65/121, PS65/132 are unbranched, unlike our current knowledge of the species (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Pena Cantero, A. L. &amp; Vervoort, W." box="[209,586,260,285]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="795 - 818" refId="ref46024" refString="Pena Cantero, A. L. &amp; Vervoort, W. (2005) Species of Schizotricha Allman, 1883 (Cnidaria: Hydrozoa: Halopterididae) from US Antarctic expeditions with the description of two new species. Journal of Natural History, 39, 795 - 818. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930400001541" type="journal article" year="2005">Peña Cantero &amp; Vervoort 2005</bibRefCitation>
). However, according to the drawings provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Allman, G. J." box="[1209,1384,260,285]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="1 - 54" refId="ref40801" refString="Allman, G. J. (1883) Report on the Hydroida dredged by H. M. S. Challenger during the years 1873 - 76. Part I. Plumularidae. Report on the scientific results of the Foyage of H. M. S. Challenger during the years 1873 - 76, Zoology, 7, 1 - 54." type="journal article" year="1883">Allman (1883)</bibRefCitation>
, the branching takes place in the very basal region of the colony. The fragmented condition of the material examined here could be masking this character. In the specimens mentioned above, there is a single nematotheca in the basal ahydrothecate internodes following hydrocladial apophyses (
<figureCitation box="[875,979,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1572,1594]" captionTargetBox="[160,1430,277,1542]" captionTargetId="figure@44.[150,1436,267,1550]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 15. a Aglaophenia baggins: hydrotheca. b–c Schizotricha glacialis: b forked hydrocladial internode; c unforked hydrocladial internode. d–f Sc. nana: d stem; e forked hydrocladial internode; f unforked hydrocladial internode. g–j Sc. unifurcata: g stem; h forked hydrocladial internode; i unforked hydrocladial internode; j internode with two hydrothecae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2608557/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Fig. 15h</figureCitation>
) (but two in the basal ahydrothecate internodes following caulinar apophyses), unlike previous descriptions of the species, which reported two nematothecae in basal ahydrothecate internodes. No differences in number of nematothecae among basal ahydrothecate internodes according to location were mentioned by previous authors. Additionally, some hydrocladial internodes are provided with two consecutive hydrothecae (
<figureCitation box="[994,1087,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1572,1594]" captionTargetBox="[160,1430,277,1542]" captionTargetId="figure@44.[150,1436,267,1550]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 15. a Aglaophenia baggins: hydrotheca. b–c Schizotricha glacialis: b forked hydrocladial internode; c unforked hydrocladial internode. d–f Sc. nana: d stem; e forked hydrocladial internode; f unforked hydrocladial internode. g–j Sc. unifurcata: g stem; h forked hydrocladial internode; i unforked hydrocladial internode; j internode with two hydrothecae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2608557/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Fig. 15j</figureCitation>
), while a single one has been mentioned by previous contributions (e.g. Peña Cantero 
<emphasis box="[824,886,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">et al.</emphasis>
1996). This character variation has also been reported for 
<taxonomicName authority="Billard, 1906" authorityName="Billard" authorityYear="1906" box="[296,692,583,608]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Halopterididae" genus="Schizotricha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="turqueti">
<emphasis box="[296,533,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Schizotricha turqueti</emphasis>
Billard, 1906
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Pena Cantero, A. L. &amp; Vervoort, W." box="[756,1118,583,608]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="795 - 818" refId="ref46024" refString="Pena Cantero, A. L. &amp; Vervoort, W. (2005) Species of Schizotricha Allman, 1883 (Cnidaria: Hydrozoa: Halopterididae) from US Antarctic expeditions with the description of two new species. Journal of Natural History, 39, 795 - 818. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930400001541" type="journal article" year="2005">Peña Cantero &amp; Vervoort 2005</bibRefCitation>
). We have considered these observations as minor variations, and we assign all the material examined to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Allman" authorityYear="1883" box="[1012,1168,620,644]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Halopterididae" genus="Schizotricha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="unifurcata">
<emphasis box="[1012,1168,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Sc. unifurcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with confidence.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="45" pageNumber="46" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1437,151,717]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
